{"questionId":"9072907","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Three identical light bulbs, X, Y and Z, each of resistance 4.0 Ω are connected to a cell of emf 12 V. The cell has negligible internal resistance.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/31b0a518196ccb5f1059cd64695552eef480e753.png\"></span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">The switch S is initially open. Calculate the total power dissipated in the circuit.</span></p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">total resistance of circuit is 8.0 «Ω» ✔<br></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">P =&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{{{12}^2}}}{{8.0}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow>\n            <mn>12</mn>\n          </mrow>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>8.0</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span> =18 «W» ✔</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","meta":{"questionId":"9072907","referenceCode":"19M.2.SL.TZ2.4a","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"The switch S is initially open. Calculate the total power dissipated in the circuit.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 5: Electricity and magnetism","5.2 – Heating effect of electric currents","Core","Topic 5: Electricity and magnetism"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}